package controllers

// Lineage-driven payload dump (golden file) for the controller's state
// machine. Each lineage starts at <none>, drives the AM through a
// sequence of production-equivalent steps (handler writes or Reconcile
// ticks), and records the (state, op, message, reason) tuple after every
// step. The full set of lineages is rendered to a self-contained HTML
// document (state_flow_pushed_messages.html) and compared byte-for-byte
// against the committed golden file in source.
//
// state_flow_pushed_messages.html is fully generated by this test —
// CSS, JS, layout and data are all driven from Go. Do not edit the file
// by hand: any change will be overwritten the next time the test runs
// with STATE_FLOW_UPDATE=1. Adjust renderHTML / htmlHeadTmpl /
// htmlTailTmpl in this file if you want to evolve the visual
// presentation.
//
// To intentionally accept a production behaviour change:
//
//	STATE_FLOW_UPDATE=1 go test ./controllers/ -run TestStateFlow_Lineages_Payloads -count=1
//
// The command (re)generates state_flow_pushed_messages.html from
// scratch. Review the diff and commit. If the file does not exist yet
// (fresh checkout, accidental deletion), the same command will create
// it; running without STATE_FLOW_UPDATE=1 against a missing file fails
// with a hint to re-run with the flag.

